                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks and recreation &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Royal Oak is located close to Canmore as well as Banff Trail, making it the ideal location for families to like to get away on the weekends. Apart from easy access to these facilities, the community is also home to several parks and playgrounds. </p>
                    <p>Some of the parks you can find within and near the community include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Royal Oak School Park</li>
                        <li>Royal Oak Pointe Park</li>
                        <li>Royal Oak Dr NW Park</li>
                        <li>Royal Birch Cres NW Playground</li>
                        <li>Royal Oak Cir NW Playground</li>
                        <li>Royal Oak Dr NW Playground</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>There are a variety of other amenities residents can enjoy other than parks.</p>
                    <p>The landmark Shane Homes YMCA at Rocky Ridge is within walking distance of Royal Oak residents. This YMCA, which is located just north of Royal Oak and features a magnificent wave design, offers a variety of recreational and leisure options through aquatics, athletics and fitness facilities, and multi-purpose rooms. With a licenced childcare facility and a Calgary Public Library, there is also a significant concentration on arts and learning.</p>
                    <p>Some other amenities you can enjoy around Royal Oak include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Shopping at the Royal Oak Shopping Plaza</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Shopping at Crowfoot crossing that boasts of all kinds of shops and services, including groceries, a movie theater, restaurants, cafés, and much more.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Shopping at the Beacon Hill shopping district that has anchors such as Home Depot, Costco, and Canadian Tire.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
