        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Royal Oak was founded in 1997 after the property was ceded to the City of Calgary in the year 1989 (from the Municipal District of Rocky View).</p>
            <p>Royal Oak had a community of 11,650 people living in 4,011 homes in the 2014 municipal census, up 6.1% from its 2011 demographic of 10,979.</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 37 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Royal Oak has an average of 2.9 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 50% female and male residents. Only 7% of the residents of Royal Oak are above the age of 65, compared to 10% for the rest of Calgary.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Royal Oak homes include two-story houses, condominiums, split levels, townhomes, and bungalows, and it is one of the newest neighbourhoods in the northwest to be constructed. The majority of the housing in this area of Calgary was constructed after the year 2000 when the city's greatest construction boom occurred.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Subdivision Areas</h3>
            <p>Royal Oak is made up of the Royal Oak Estates subdivision in the south, the Royal Elm and Royal Highlands subdivisions in the middle, and the Cascades subdivision in the north.</p>
        </div>
